Telecom Italia, Oi, Embratel Made Bids for AES Atimus, Sole Says

-- B y   S o n i a   S i r l e t t i
-- 
2011-06-02T07:07:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-02/telecom-italia-oi-embratel-made-bids-for-aes-atimus-sole-says.html
Telecom Italia SpA (TIT) ,  Tele Norte Leste
Participacoes SA (TNLP3) , known as Oi, and  Embratel Participacoes SA (EBTP3) 
each made a binding offer to buy AES Atimus, a Brazilian
telecommunications-infrastructure company,  Il Sole 24 Ore 
reported without saying where it got the information.  Telecom Italia, which bid through local unit  Tim
Participacoes SA (TCSL4) , made the highest offer at 1.6 billion reais
($1 billion), according to the Italian daily.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sonia Sirletti in Milan at 
 ssirletti@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Frank Connelly at   fconnelly@bloomberg.net  